---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Security & Privacy - Jakarta Migration MCP"
  description="Security and privacy guarantees for Jakarta Migration MCP. Learn how we handle your code and data."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 via-white to-primary-50/30 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">Security & Privacy</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Your code and project data are handled with the utmost care. We understand that Java developers 
        working with enterprise codebases need complete confidence in the security and privacy of their 
        intellectual property.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Q&A Section -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">Explicit Security & Privacy Posture</h2>
      
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-green-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
            <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Does this tool send code off-machine?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2 font-semibold">Answer: No (when running locally)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              When using the local STDIO setup, your code never leaves your machine. All analysis is performed 
              locally with zero network calls.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
            <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-blue-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-7-4a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zM9 9a1 1 0 000 2v3a1 1 0 001 1h1a1 1 0 100-2v-3a1 1 0 00-1-1H9z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Does it require internet access?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2 font-semibold">Answer: Only for hosted service</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              The local STDIO version runs completely offline. The hosted Apify service requires internet 
              access for the API call, but your code is processed in isolated, ephemeral containers that 
              are destroyed immediately after processing.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-green-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
            <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Does it collect telemetry?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2 font-semibold">Answer: No telemetry by default</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              We don't collect, track, or analyze your code. Each request is processed independently with 
              no memory of previous requests. No usage tracking, analytics, or code scanning for any purpose 
              other than migration analysis.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-green-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
            <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can it run offline?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2 font-semibold">Answer: Yes (local setup)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              The local STDIO setup runs 100% locally with no network calls. Everything runs on your machine 
              with complete control and visibility.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-green-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4">
            <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What data touches Stripe?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2 font-semibold">Answer: Payment information only</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Stripe is only used for payment processing. Your code, project files, or analysis results never 
              touch Stripe. Only billing information (if you choose to use premium features) is processed 
              through Stripe.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stateless Architecture Section -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Stateless Architecture</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-green-600 mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900">No Data Persistence</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">The service is completely stateless. Your project files, source code, and analysis results are never stored, logged, or persisted on our servers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-green-600 mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900">No Data Collection</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">We don't collect, track, or analyze your code. Each request is processed independently with no memory of previous requests.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-green-600 mr-3 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Local Execution Option</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">For maximum privacy, you can run the entire service locally using the local STDIO setup. Your code never leaves your machine.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Hosted Service Section -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Hosted Service (Apify)</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        When using the Apify-hosted service:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Analysis is performed in isolated, ephemeral containers</li>
        <li>All containers are destroyed immediately after processing</li>
        <li>No persistent storage is used</li>
        <li>Your API token is only used for authentication and billing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local Service Section -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50/50 to-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Local Service</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
        When running locally via STDIO:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>100% Local</strong> - Everything runs on your machine</li>
        <li><strong>No Network Calls</strong> - No external requests are made</li>
        <li><strong>Complete Control</strong> - You have full visibility and control over the process</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Recommendation Section -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-600 to-primary-700 py-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-2">
          For maximum security and privacy, we recommend using the local STDIO setup for sensitive projects.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
